column5: XRT gonna make a guess here for tomorrow Mexico and US are working on details but US wants a mechanism to hold Mexico accountable if they do not act controls Not going to settle with a promise we know they need the trafficking in persons and smuggling business intact I think it wont happen tonight or tomorrow morning and its just one more setback Also China counter has not materialized but its mouthpiece has spoken today and said its soon To me thats actionable and not something to ignore They appeared soft when they came out with a white paper instead of a blacklist but that had a negative effect they need to do more than fine FEDEX and its what Im expecting they do

Feds Beige Book was a little more upbeat than the prior report as analysts expected The economy expanded at a modest pace overall and showed a slight improvement versus the prior period said the report Almost all Districts reported some growth and a few saw moderate gains Consumer spending was generally positive but tempered Additionally manufacturing reports were generally positive though there were some signs of slowing and a more uncertain outlook Construction showed overall growth Agricultural conditions remained weak The outlook for the coming months was solidly positive but modest with little variation among reporting Districts Meanwhile employment continued to increase across the nation but tight labor markets continued to constrain Despite some pressure from competition for workers wages pressures remained relatively subdued Prices continued to increase at a modest pace SPY ESF XRT RTH USOShow More
